Description: Wall sherd of North Ionian pottery bowl; interior glazed, fired orange; traces of red-white lines with irregular red blobs below; exterior: cream slip, brownish paint; stopt meander running left between dividing bands; rays below and dab of glaze preserved in frieze above; inscription cut on interior.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.211)
